      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GYM QUEEN (4) found one better two runs back then made mistakes last time when she broke and finished 30 metres back in fifth over 2180m at Kilmore. Won't find this any harder so she can return to form. RIPPING RONALDO (8) finished sixth two runs ago then broke and finished a long last over 1650m at Bendigo at the latest appearance. Will enjoy a pretty soft run from this draw, with the sprint lane to play a big role. Meets a similar line up so he is sure to be a force if the manners improve. SPESHAL (2) is close to a win after two successive placings, the latest a third over 2100m at Charlton. Great chance to break through. ARIVADERCHI (3) is in the mix following a fourth at his most recent appearance over 2190m at this track.",
